China has allocated 200 million yuan for disaster relief after a devastating earthquake in Sichuan province killed over 8,700 people.
The quake, with a magnitude of 7.8, struck densely populated areas including Chengdu.
Russian President Dmitry Medvedev offered condolences and assistance to China.
The ASEAN Inter-Parliamentary Assembly and Vietnam also expressed sympathy and support.
Germany and Norway pledged financial aid, with Germany providing 500,000 euros and Norway providing 20 million krone.
Belgium offered 250,000 euros in relief funds.
The death toll is expected to rise as thousands remain buried and missing in the debris.
